                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/142.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Leishman says owing to interrupted telegraphic communication he has not
                    received report from vice consul at Mersina, whom he instructed to go to Adana,
                    but fears rumors are true, as the information <pb facs="0638" n="566"
                        xml:id="pg_566"/> which leaks through indicates serious disturbances which
                    have extended to surrounding towns, including Tarsus. He adds that he is
                    bringing all pressure possible to bear on Porte, and that French and English
                    Governments are sending ships to Mersina.</p>
            </div>
